    <SectionSubTitle title="Guard Skill Interactions" />

    <p>
      So when you compare blocking attacks with guard level 0, using normal block and perfect guard,
      you will notice that the perfect guard results in less chip damage and faster recovery. This
      is because I assume that perfect guard has some sort of build-in guard levels. If you start
      including guard levels, it will start to get weird though, as it doesn't seem to scale with
      it.
    </p>

