    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Guard Dash (GD)">
    <p>
      Guard Dash is also back in this game, but because of the triple thrust finisher and the nerf
      of leaping thrust, it barely sees any use.
    </p>

    <p>
      Even when you want to use it as a gap closer, like in some older games, you know have better
      options, as you can perform a leaping thrust out of neutral, by pressing both poke buttons at
      the same time. And most of the time this distance is enough, making it a better option because
      you deal damage and it's faster than doing a guard dash into a leaping thrust.
    </p>

    <p>
      Unless you need the extra mobility range or defensive coverage during positioning, alternative
      gap closers generally prove more efficient and damaging.
    </p>
  </Section>
